ManyToMany requires a mapping table. The code should look like
```
@Entity
public class Brand {
   @ManyToMany(mappedBy = &quot;brands&quot;)
    @JsonIgnore
    private List&lt;Category&gt; categories;
}

@Entity
public class Category {
    @ManyToMany
	@JoinTable(
		name = &quot;Category_Brand&quot;, 
		joinColumns = { @JoinColumn(name = &quot;category_id&quot;) }, 
		inverseJoinColumns = { @JoinColumn(name = &quot;brand_id&quot;) }
    )
    @JsonIgnore
    private List&lt;Brand&gt; brands;
}
```
mappedBy must point to a field in the other entity.

This was the first issue which I ran into while mapping Many to Many Relationship with Hibernate and sadly it **nothing to do with Entity Mapping**.

Let&#39;s forget the Hibernate for a moment and verify the class structure.

Product that has a Category `private Category category;`
Category has a list of Brands `List&lt;Brand&gt; Brands;`
Brand has a list of Categories `List&lt;Category&gt; categories;`

When you do `System.out.println(p);` it calls p.toString() 
This means it makes call to `category.toString()`, 
This then makes call to `Brands.toString()` 
Each brand has a list of Categories so `categories.toString()` is called.
Now each category a list of Brands so `brands.toString()` is called.
And the cycle continues.

I understand that you&#39;ve used `@JsonIgnore` to avoid this problem while Serializing the object but while doing toString() recursive calls are being made. 

There may be other ways of addressing this but below are the two ways I solved it:

 - **Override the `toString()` method and exclude the list**

You can explicitly override the `toString()` method &amp; exclude the list from being part of the String retuned by the default toString() 

 - **Annotate your the fields with [`@ToString.Exclude`][1] lombok**

If you are using lombok to generate toString(), you can annotate these lists with [`@ToString.Exclude`][1] to exclude it from being part of the String retuned by the toString() method generated by Lombok.

    public class Brand {
       @ToString.Exclude    
       @ManyToMany(mappedBy = &quot;productCompanyList&quot;)
        @JsonIgnore
        private List&lt;Category&gt; categories;
    }
    
    public class Category {
        @ManyToMany
        @Column(nullable = false)
        @ToString.Exclude
        @JsonIgnore
        private List&lt;Brand&gt; Brands;
    }

  [1]: https://projectlombok.org/api/lombok/ToString.Exclude.html
  [2]: https://github.com/ssadhukhanv2/hints

