Although the initial intuition is good, this is not what Exceptions are used for. Exceptions are generally used to signal errors that happen in the VM and should generally not be used to create logic flows. 

The easiest way would be to turn your function into a boolean function
```java
boolean checkAge() {
    if (age &lt; 18) {
        return false;
    }
    else {
        return true;
    }
}
```

Which can then be used in your `main` function as such
```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
  int age = 20;
  if(checkAge(age)){
     System.out.println(&quot;Access granted - You are old enough!&quot;);
  } else {
     System.out.println(&quot;Access denied - You must be at least 18 years old.&quot;);
  }
}
```
